                <head>199. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The Protocol for the Prolongation of the International Sugar Agreement of 1958
                    was completed in London on August 1, 1963. The United States signed it on
                    September 27. The Senate gave its advice and consent to ratification on January
                    30, 1964, and the Protocol entered into force for the United States on February
                    27. According to the Protocol, the International Sugar Agreement would remain in
                    effect until December 31, 1965, unless a new agreement had been negotiated
                    before that date. For text, see 15 <gloss target="#t_UST1">UST</gloss> 2512;
                    TIAS 5744. Documentation on the ratification of the Protocol is in Department of
                    State, Central Files, INCO–SUGAR 4.</p>
            </div>
